accountDescription: Liquid assets available for business operations.
statement: Cash on hand and in bank accounts.
comment: Highly liquid asset used for daily business transactions.

accountDescription: Money owed by customers for goods or services provided.
statement: Amounts due from customers within a year.
comment: Current asset expected to be converted into cash.

accountDescription: Advance payment for future rent obligations.
statement: Rent paid in advance, yet to be incurred.
comment: Will be expensed as rent becomes due.

accountDescription: Advance payment for insurance coverage.
statement: Insurance premiums paid in advance for future coverage.
comment: Expensed over the insurance coverage period.

accountDescription: Items used in daily operations.
statement: Office supplies on hand.
comment: Will be expensed as supplies are consumed.

accountDescription: Long-term assets used in business operations.
statement: Furniture, computers, and other office equipment.
comment: Depreciated over time.

accountDescription: Cumulative depreciation of office equipment.
statement: Total depreciation of equipment.
comment: Contra-asset reducing the value of office equipment.

accountDescription: Obligations to pay for goods or services received.
statement: Amounts owed to suppliers.
comment: Short-term liabilities for purchases made on credit.

accountDescription: Salaries owed to employees for services rendered.
statement: Employee salaries owed but not yet paid.
comment: Short-term liability to employees.

accountDescription: Revenue received but not yet earned.
statement: Cash received in advance for services to be performed.
comment: Will be recognized as revenue when services are provided.

accountDescription: Equity contributed by owners of the business.
statement: Owner's initial investment in the business.
comment: Represents ownership interest in the company.

accountDescription: Dividends declared but not yet paid to shareholders.
statement: Dividends owed to shareholders.
comment: Liability until dividends are paid.

accountDescription: Income from services rendered to clients.
statement: Revenue earned from providing services.
comment: Primary source of revenue for the business.

accountDescription: Costs associated with insurance premiums.
statement: Expenses related to insurance coverage.
comment: Recurring expense for business risk management.

accountDescription: Costs related to the depreciation of office equipment.
statement: Annual depreciation of office equipment.
comment: Non-cash expense that reflects the wear and tear of long-term assets.

accountDescription: Costs associated with renting office space.
statement: Expenses related to office rental payments.
comment: Recurring monthly rental expense.

accountDescription: Costs related to the consumption of office supplies.
statement: Expenses incurred for office supplies usage.
comment: Supplies used for business operations.

accountDescription: Salaries paid to employees for services rendered.
statement: Total salaries paid during the accounting period.
comment: Major operational expense for the business.

accountDescription: Costs associated with telephone and communication services.
statement: Expenses related to communication services such as phone bills.
comment: Recurring expense for business communication.

accountDescription: Costs related to utilities such as electricity, water, and gas.
statement: Utility expenses incurred for the business.
comment: Recurring expense for basic business operations.

accountDescription: Costs related to promoting the business.
statement: Expenses incurred for advertising and marketing.
comment: Used for campaigns to increase brand awareness and sales.
